# 🛡️ Spam Detection using Naive Bayes

This project demonstrates a simple machine learning model to detect whether a given comment is **spam** or **not spam**. The model uses the **Multinomial Naive Bayes** classifier and **CountVectorizer** for text processing.

---

## 📂 Files

- `spamdetection.ipynb`: Jupyter Notebook containing all the code for preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and user input prediction.
- `README.md`: Project documentation.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Train a spam classifier on example comments.
- Predict whether a new comment is spam or not.
- Print classification metrics: precision, recall, F1-score, and accuracy.
- Accepts user input to predict in real-time.

---

## 📊 Model Details

- **Algorithm**: Multinomial Naive Bayes
- **Vectorization**: CountVectorizer (Bag-of-Words)
- **Evaluation**: Classification Report (Precision, Recall, F1)

